<pre><code>class SomeClass {   var someProperty: Int {     throw Err("SNAFU")   } } </code></pre>  <p>For code like the above, the swift binary complains 'error is not handled because the enclosing function is not declared 'throws'.</p>  <p>How do I declare that 'someProperty' 'throws' in the above?</p>  <pre><code>class SomeClass {   var someProperty throws: Int {   } } </code></pre>  <p>and</p>  <pre><code>class SomeClass {   var someProperty: throws Int {   } } </code></pre>  <p>and</p>  <pre><code>class SomeClass {   var someProperty: Int throws {   } } </code></pre>  <p>don't seem to work.</p>